23_14	0.090699934	Folkman said Monday that in about 80 cancer patients, mostly children, the drugs destroyed growths that would have killed them.
23_15	0.095375588	``If we'd given up in the first month or two, they wouldn't be around,'' he said.
23_16	0.087974756	One of the most dramatic cases was that of a Vermont teenager who in 1998 had a volleyball-sized pelvic tumor that resisted all therapies.
